snippet.textDisplay:
Okay, I heard a rumor that the guy was a flat earther, and I've dug enough to call it plausible. However, this is still really sad.

Thinking on it, man... what if he'd gone up into space or something with an actual rocket later? He could've learned. Could've seen it for himself. Could've had his eyes opened to the wonders of our cosmos...

I lament his passing. While I think it foolish to believe the earth flat and do stigmatize it, the man was, just maybe, setting himself up to see it for himself, which is hella more than I can say about most flat-earthers who would rather talk than check. I can find respect for a man in that, even if they're stubborn as a mule.

So, R.I.P old dude, and hey... if nothing else, think about it. Your grave can read, "I died riding a motherfucking rocket into the atmosphere. Say what you will about my misguided reasons, but you will never be able to say that your balls are that big."

Probably more awesome than my out is gonna be.
